    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-10T14:22:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-06T00:34:00-05:00" n="249"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1989</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Irkutsk</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HEL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d249fn1">Sent via the Consulates at Vladivostok and
                        Kobe.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Irkutsk</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1918-06-10T15:22:00-04:00"
                            notBefore="1918-06-06T14:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 10, 1918, 3.22
                        p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following from [<persName corresp="#p_ECGH1">Emerson</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_SMHH1">Slaughter</persName>,] Suslovo near Mariinsk: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>On return Mariinsk June 2<note n="2" xml:id="d249fn2">See telegram of
                                June 15, 2 p.m., from the Consul at Vladivostok, <hi rend="italic"
                                    >post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_212">p. 212</ref>.</note> found
                            Czechs and Russians reenforcing, strongly entrenched, 3,500 Czechs,
                            2,500 Russians ready fight. We attempted mediate, secured armistice
                            until June 10. Now going Vladivostok with Russian and Czech
                            representatives secure final settlement. Russians will never agree
                            permit Czechs proceed fully armed; Czechs want to learn [<hi
                                rend="italic">sic</hi>], rear trains safe to [omission]. White
                            Guards Novo Nikolaevsk, Tomsk, Mariinsk, taken advantage <pb facs="0282"
                                n="192" xml:id="pg_192"/> situation to arm and take control places
                            named. Czechs refuse permit Russians resume authority places prior their
                            departure. Details by <persName>Thomas</persName> leaving to-day.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
